BUG 1 — Project ID dropdown: background/text broken in dark mode
==============================================================================
ROOT CAUSE: The suggestions <ul> for project autocomplete uses inline 
backgroundColor: '#ffffff' which is always white regardless of theme.
In dark mode, white background with slate-900 inherited text = unreadable.

FIX: Replace ALL inline style colors in the project dropdown with 
theme-aware Tailwind classes. Strip every inline style color/background 
from the dropdown elements and replace with explicit Tailwind classes that 
cover both light and dark:

  <ul className="absolute z-[200] mt-1 w-full 
    bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 
    border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 
    rounded-xl shadow-xl shadow-black/10 dark:shadow-black/40
    max-h-52 overflow-auto
    ring-1 ring-black/5 dark:ring-white/5">
    
    {suggestions.map(suggestion => (
      <li
        key={suggestion.value}
        onMouseDown={() => handleSuggestionSelect(field.name, suggestion)}
        className="px-3 py-2.5 cursor-pointer transition-colors duration-100
          text-[13px] font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200
          hover:bg-blue-50 dark:hover:bg-blue-500/10
          hover:text-blue-700 dark:hover:text-blue-300
          first:rounded-t-xl last:rounded-b-xl"
      >
        <div className="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100">
          {suggestion.label}
        </div>
        {suggestion.description && (
          <div className="text-[11px] text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mt-0.5">
            {suggestion.description}
          </div>
        )}
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>

  "No results" state:
  <div className="absolute z-[200] mt-1 w-full px-3 py-2.5
    bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 
    border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 
    rounded-xl shadow-xl text-[12px] 
    text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">
    No results found
  </div>

REMOVE: Every instance of style={{ backgroundColor: '#ffffff' }}, 
style={{ color: '#1e293b' }}, style={{ color: '#64748b' }} inside 
the dropdown. Zero inline style colors remaining.

