BUG 3 — Dark mode: form content colors overlapping / unreadable
==============================================================================
ROOT CAUSE: Some text elements inside FormRenderer.jsx are missing dark: 
variants, so they render dark text on dark backgrounds in dark mode.

AUDIT every text-* and bg-* class in the file. For any class that 
specifies only a light-mode color, add the dark: counterpart.

Specific classes to audit and fix:
- Any text-slate-700 without dark:text-slate-200 → add dark:text-slate-200
- Any text-slate-600 without dark:text-slate-300 → add dark:text-slate-300
- Any text-slate-900 without dark:text-slate-100 → add dark:text-slate-100
- Any bg-white without dark:bg-slate-800 or dark:bg-slate-700/30 → add it
- Any bg-slate-50 without dark:bg-slate-700/30 → add it
- Any border-slate-200 without dark:border-slate-700 → add it
- Error banner: ensure both bg-red-50 AND dark:bg-red-500/10 are present
- Table row backgrounds: bg-slate-50 → add dark:bg-slate-700/20

After this audit, there should be NO element in FormRenderer.jsx 
that has only a light-mode color class without a dark: counterpart.

