BUG 4 — Horizontal scroll at bottom
==============================================================================
ROOT CAUSE: The form's max-w-[480px] is wider than the chat bubble container 
on smaller screens, causing overflow. The chat overlay has px-4 md:px-12 
padding but message bubbles have max-w constraints that may be narrower than 480px.

FIX:

A. Change form wrapper from max-w-[480px] to max-w-full:
   The form should FILL its container, not overflow it.
   
   className="w-full rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700/80 
   bg-white dark:bg-slate-800/80 shadow-lg shadow-black/5 dark:shadow-black/20 
   backdrop-blur-sm p-4 my-2"

B. Find where FormRenderer is rendered inside ChatOverlay.jsx (inside 
   MessageBubble or the form message type branch). Ensure its container div has:
   className="w-full max-w-[520px]"
   This gives a max-width cap at the parent level, not the form component level.

C. Inside the form, any fixed-width elements (e.g., table columns with w-32 
   or w-48) should be changed to use percentage or min-w + flex instead.
   Table columns should use: className="min-w-0 flex-1" not fixed pixel widths.

D. Add overflow-x: hidden to the form wrapper as a safety net:
   Add style={{ overflowX: 'hidden' }} on the outer form container div.

